Disk Forensics > [T9]: Exploring ShimCache: Uncovering Application Compatibility Insights

(5) ShimCache aka AppCompatCache

ShimCache is a feature in the operating system that allows older applications to run on newer systems. To check if an application uses ShimCache, you can go to the properties section of the program and click on the Compatibility tab. There, you should see an option to "Run this program in compatibility mode for" which indicates whether ShimCache is used or not.

 

 

This information is stored in the registry under the "HKLM\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\SessionManager\AppCompatCache\AppCompatCache" key.

You can use the "ShimCacheParser" tool by Mandiant to parse the AppCompatCache data from the SYSTEM hive into a CSV file. This file can then be viewed using the "Timeline Explorer" tool. By examining the AppCompatCache data, you can gain insights into the applications that have been run in compatibility mode on the system.
